name: FInterchangeMeshGeometry
doc: * A mesh geometry is a description of a translated mesh asset node that defines a geometry.

MeshUid: The unique ID of the UInterchangeMeshNode represented by this structure.
MeshNode: The UInterchangeMeshNode pointer represented by this structure.
ReferencingMeshInstanceUids: All mesh instances that refer to this UInterchangeMeshNode pointer.
AttachedSocketUids: A list of all scene nodes that represent sockets attached to this mesh.
